{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/shared/error.rs:299-305` now maps every `AppError::BackendUnavailable` to `FailureClass::BinaryNotFound`. That variant is reused for non-binary outages and config/auth errors, for example `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1164-1172` (missing `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`), `src/adapters/openrouter_backend.rs:326-333` (401/403), and `src/adapters/github.rs:613-624` (GitHub HTTP/JSON failures). After this change those unrelated failures are all mislabeled as `binary_not_found` and become terminal/non-retryable. Restrict `BinaryNotFound` to the actual spawn/exit-127 paths and keep other `BackendUnavailable` cases in their existing class.","rationale":"This turns a local retry-policy tweak into a repo-wide semantic change and can disable retries or misreport operator-facing failures far outside the process backend."},{"body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:4620-4654` regresses cancellation handling during the new retry backoff. If `cancellation_token` fires inside the `tokio::select!`, the code falls through to `fail_run_result(&error, ...)`, so the run is recorded as the prior backend failure instead of `cancellation`. `cargo test --features test-stub --test unit workflow_engine_test::cancellation_between_retry_attempts_does_not_start_next_attempt` now fails with `transport_failure` vs `cancellation`. Return a cancellation error from this branch (or plumb cancellation into `fail_run_result`) before recording the terminal run failure.","rationale":"User-initiated stops during retry delay are no longer distinguishable from backend failures."},{"body":"`src/adapters/process_backend.rs:352-369`, `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1021-1025`, and `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1434-1437` only signal the direct child PID on timeout/cancel. Any grandchildren spawned by `claude`/`codex` survive as orphaned processes after the parent is SIGKILLed. The tmux adapter already targets the process group in `src/adapters/tmux.rs:990-1002`; process-backend needs equivalent process-group setup/teardown before we can say timed-out backend invocations are actually killed.","rationale":"Without group termination, repeated timeouts can leak backend helpers and leave the machine in a bad state."},{"body":"`tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs:1089-1092`, `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs:1157-1160`, `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs:1468-1470`, and `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs:3084-3086` still assert 4 stage entries after changing the stub failure count from 3 to 5. With the higher retry budget the failed run now enters the stage 5 times and the resumed run adds a 6th entry, so these tests fail under `cargo test --features test-stub --test unit workflow_engine_test::resume_from_failed_*`.","rationale":"The patch does not currently meet the acceptance criterion that the test suite passes."}],"summary":"Reviewed the retry-hardening changes and found four actionable issues: a too-broad `BackendUnavailable` -> `BinaryNotFound` remap, a cancellation/backoff regression in the engine, timeout cleanup that only kills the direct child process, and stale workflow-engine test expectations that now fail with `--features test-stub`."}